# Frontend / React Code

Read with `50-code-quality.mdc` and the `design` skill (`.cursor/core/skills/domains/design/SKILL.md`).

## Components stay thin; logic lives in hooks

A component renders. Non-trivial logic (data fetching, derived state, side effects, event orchestration) goes into a **custom hook** or a plain function, not inline in JSX.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — fetching, filtering, formatting all inline in the component
function Orders() {
  const [data, setData] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => { fetch("/api/orders").then(r => r.json()).then(setData); }, []);
  const visible = data.filter(o => o.status === "open").map(o => ({ ...o, total: o.items.reduce(...) }));
  return <ul>{visible.map(o => <li key={o.id}>{o.total}</li>)}</ul>;
}

// ✅ GOOD — logic in a hook, component just renders
function Orders() {
  const { orders, isLoading, error } = useOpenOrders();
  if (isLoading) return <OrdersSkeleton />;
  if (error) return <OrdersError error={error} />;
  return <OrderList orders={orders} />;
}
```

## Server vs client boundary

- Default to **Server Components**; add `"use client"` only where interactivity/browser APIs are needed, as low in the tree as possible.
- Never embed secrets or server-only logic in client components. Fetch on the server; pass typed props down.

## Lists call a single-item component

Rendering a collection maps to one item component — `items.map(i => <Item key={i.id} item={i} />)` — not flat per-item markup + logic inside the loop (mirrors the single-handler rule in `50-code-quality.mdc`).

## Styling — tokens, mobile-first, accessible

- Use **design tokens** (Tailwind theme scale: spacing, color, type) — no magic px/hex. Extend the theme rather than sprinkling arbitrary values (`p-[13px]`, `text-[#3a3a3a]`).
- **Mobile-first:** base styles target 320–375px, scale up with `sm: md: lg:`. Touch targets ≥ 44×44px.
- Accessible by default: semantic HTML, labels on inputs, alt text, visible focus, WCAG AA contrast, keyboard operable.
- **i18n:** never hardcode UI strings — externalize; expect text expansion and RTL.

## Reusability

- Reuse existing components before creating new ones; extract shared UI into one place.
- Keep props typed and minimal; lift shared state deliberately, don't prop-drill deep chains.

## Anti-patterns

- Fat components with fetching/business logic inline in JSX.
- `"use client"` at the top of the tree by default; secrets in client code.
- Arbitrary Tailwind values instead of theme tokens; desktop-first then "make it responsive."
- Hardcoded strings; missing loading/error/empty states; sub-44px touch targets.
